    # Midodrine evidence in cirrhosis (101-115)
    "Midodrine is an oral alpha-1 adrenergic agonist that constricts arteriolar and venous smooth muscle, increasing systemic vascular resistance and venous return, directly counteracting the vasodilation of cirrhosis.",
    "In cirrhosis, midodrine at 7.5 mg TID raised MAP by an average of 10-12 mmHg and reduced plasma renin activity by approximately 40% in the landmark study by Singh et al., indicating improved EABV.",
