    # Exercise physiology in cirrhosis (131-145)
    "Peak oxygen consumption (VO2 peak) in cirrhosis is reduced to 50-70% of predicted, correlating with disease severity, sarcopenia, cardiac dysfunction, and autonomic impairment.",
    "The reduced VO2 peak in cirrhosis results from peripheral factors (decreased muscle mass and mitochondrial function) more than cardiac limitations, distinguishing it from primary heart failure.",
    "Anaerobic threshold is reached earlier in cirrhosis patients during graded exercise, meaning they rely on anaerobic metabolism at lower workloads, producing excessive lactate and fatigue.",
